  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Government and CSO Capacity to Combat TIP</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on IOM&#x2019;s recently concluded trafficking in person (TIP) project, IMPACT project will be implemented across 11 districts in Sri Lanka. The project goal is to strengthen national and community level capacities, scale up community driven responses to effectively combat and respond to TIP and contribute to the effective implementation of the National Strategic Action Plan to monitor and combat human trafficking. The project will adopt a victim centric and survivor informed approach. A wide array of activities including public awareness campaigns, trainings for government officials and non-government stakeholders, assistance to victims, support to upgrade shelters and investigation agencies, interventions to combat child trafficking, technical support to the Government&apos;s National Anti-Human Trafficking Task Force, strengthening national referral mechanisms, engaging with private sector tourism service providers to prevent trafficking, will be implemented under the project.</narrative>
  </description>
